\par Harry made his way down to the end-of-year feast alone that night. He had been held up by Madam Pomfrey\rquote s fussing about, insisting on giving him one last checkup, so the Great Hall was already full. It was decked out in the S
lytherin colors of green and silver to cel\-ebrate Slytherin\rquote s winning the House Cup for the seventh year in a row. A huge banner showing the Slytherin serpent covered the wall behind the High Table.
\par When Harry walked in there was a sudden hush, and then everybody started talking loudly at once. He slipped into a seat be\-tween Ron and Hermione at the Gryffindor table and tried to ig\-nore the fact that people were standing up to look at him.
\par Fortunately, Dumbledore arrived moments later. The babble died away.
\par \'93Another year gone!\'94 Dumbledore said cheerfully. \'93And I must trouble you with an old man\rquote 
